But in my experience the people who get confused and screw things up, tend to be the same ones who stand in the 8 items or less line at the supermarket with 40 items in their cart.<br>
<br>
Never underestimate the power of human stupidity.<br>
<br>
KCoG raids are inheirently inefficent.  Not much that you can do about it.  How well they run depends on luck, and the general ability of the raid leader to keep complete and total control over the raid.  How they do that differs from leader to leader, and there's no single best way.<br>
<br>
But you can make systems all day long.  They can make sense and look like they'll work.  But without a good, strong leader even the best system will fail.  And with a good, strong leader even a weak system can work well.<br>
<br>
